You can specify `timeout` in milliseconds to automatically abort a request after a timeout (default is disabled).

```ts
await ofetch("http://google.com/404", {
  timeout: 3000, // Timeout after 3 seconds
});
```

## ✔️ Circuit Breaker

You can enable an opt-in, per-origin circuit breaker to stop hammering an unhealthy origin. When the number of consecutive failures reaches `threshold`, the circuit **opens** and further requests to that origin fail fast with a `Circuit breaker is open` error, without calling the underlying `fetch`. After `cooldown` milliseconds the circuit goes **half-open** and allows up to `halfOpenMaxRequests` probe requests through: a successful probe **closes** the circuit, a failed probe re-**opens** it and restarts the cooldown.

Circuit state is keyed by request **origin** (not path) and is shared between clients derived via `.create()`.

Enable it with defaults:

```ts
await ofetch("https://api.example.com/users", {
  circuitBreaker: true,
});
```

Or customize it:

```ts
await ofetch("https://api.example.com/users", {
  circuitBreaker: {
    threshold: 5, // consecutive failures before opening (default 5)
    cooldown: 30_000, // ms to wait before a half-open probe (default 30000)
    halfOpenMaxRequests: 1, // max concurrent probes while half-open (default 1)
    // status codes counted as circuit failures
    failureStatusCodes: [408, 409, 425, 429, 500, 502, 503, 504],
  },
});
```

A failure is counted for network errors, response parsing errors, exceptions thrown from interceptors, and responses whose status is listed in `failureStatusCodes`. Internal retries count as a single logical request, so a request that exhausts its retries records exactly one failure. When `circuitBreaker` is omitted or falsey, no circuit tracking or blocking is applied.", "originalFile": null, "structuredPatch": [{"oldStart": 136, "oldLines": 6, "newStart": 136, "newLines": 36, "lines": [" });", " ```", " ", "+## ✔️ Circuit Breaker", "+", "+You can enable an opt-in, per-origin circuit breaker to stop hammering an unhealthy origin. When the number of consecutive failures reaches `threshold`, the circuit **opens** and further requests to that origin fail fast with a `Circuit breaker is open` error, without calling the underlying `fetch`. After `cooldown` milliseconds the circuit goes **half-open** and allows up to `halfOpenMaxRequests` probe requests through: a successful probe **closes** the circuit, a failed probe re-**opens** it and restarts the cooldown.", "+", "+Circuit state is keyed by request **origin** (not path) and is shared between clients derived via `.create()`.", "+", "+Enable it with defaults:", "+", "+```ts", "+await ofetch("https://api.example.com/users", {", "+  circuitBreaker: true,", "+});", "+```", "+", "+Or customize it:", "+", "+```ts", "+await ofetch("https://api.example.com/users", {", "+  circuitBreaker: {", "+    threshold: 5, // consecutive failures before opening (default 5)", "+    cooldown: 30_000, // ms to wait before a half-open probe (default 30000)", "+    halfOpenMaxRequests: 1, // max concurrent probes while half-open (default 1)", "+    // status codes counted as circuit failures", "+    failureStatusCodes: [408, 409, 425, 429, 500, 502, 503, 504],", "+  },", "+});", "+```", "+", "+A failure is counted for network errors, response parsing errors, exceptions thrown from interceptors, and responses whose status is listed in `failur